42namespace WebCore {
43
44CachedFont::CachedFont(CachedResourceRequest&& request, PAL::SessionID sessionID, const CookieJar* cookieJar, Type type)
45 : CachedResource(WTFMove(request), type, sessionID, cookieJar)
46 , m_loadInitiated(false)
47 , m_hasCreatedFontDataWrappingResource(false)
48{
49}
50
51CachedFont::~CachedFont() = default;
52
53void CachedFont::load(CachedResourceLoader&)
54{
55 // Don't load the file yet. Wait for an access before triggering the load.
56 setLoading(true);
57}
58
59void CachedFont::didAddClient(CachedResourceClient& client)
60{
61 ASSERT(client.resourceClientType() == CachedFontClient::expectedType());
62 if (!isLoading())
63 static_cast<CachedFontClient&>(client).fontLoaded(*this);
64}
65
66void CachedFont::finishLoading(SharedBuffer* data, const NetworkLoadMetrics& metrics)
67{
68 m_data = data;
69 setEncodedSize(m_data.get() ? m_data->size() : 0);
70 setLoading(false);
71 checkNotify(metrics);
72}
73
74void CachedFont::beginLoadIfNeeded(CachedResourceLoader& loader)
75{
76 if (!m_loadInitiated) {
77 m_loadInitiated = true;
78 CachedResource::load(loader);
79 }
80}
81
82bool CachedFont::ensureCustomFontData(const AtomString&)
83{
84 return ensureCustomFontData(m_data.get());
85}
86
87String CachedFont::calculateItemInCollection() const
88{
89 return url().fragmentIdentifier().toString();
90}
91
92bool CachedFont::ensureCustomFontData(SharedBuffer* data)
93{
94 if (!m_fontCustomPlatformData && !errorOccurred() && !isLoading() && data) {
95 bool wrapping;
96 m_fontCustomPlatformData = createCustomFontData(*data, calculateItemInCollection(), wrapping);
97 m_hasCreatedFontDataWrappingResource = m_fontCustomPlatformData && wrapping;
98 if (!m_fontCustomPlatformData)
99 setStatus(DecodeError);
100 }
101
102 return m_fontCustomPlatformData.get();
103}
104
105std::unique_ptr<FontCustomPlatformData> CachedFont::createCustomFontData(SharedBuffer& bytes, const String& itemInCollection, bool& wrapping)
106{
107 auto buffer = makeRefPtr(bytes);
108 wrapping = !convertWOFFToSfntIfNecessary(buffer);
109 return buffer ? createFontCustomPlatformData(*buffer, itemInCollection) : nullptr;
110}
111
112RefPtr<Font> CachedFont::createFont(const FontDescription& fontDescription, const AtomString&, bool syntheticBold, bool syntheticItalic, const FontFeatureSettings& fontFaceFeatures, FontSelectionSpecifiedCapabilities fontFaceCapabilities)
113{
114 return Font::create(platformDataFromCustomData(fontDescription, syntheticBold, syntheticItalic, fontFaceFeatures, fontFaceCapabilities), Font::Origin::Remote);
115}
116
117FontPlatformData CachedFont::platformDataFromCustomData(const FontDescription& fontDescription, bool bold, bool italic, const FontFeatureSettings& fontFaceFeatures, FontSelectionSpecifiedCapabilities fontFaceCapabilities)
118{
119 ASSERT(m_fontCustomPlatformData);
120 return platformDataFromCustomData(*m_fontCustomPlatformData, fontDescription, bold, italic, fontFaceFeatures, fontFaceCapabilities);
121}
122
123FontPlatformData CachedFont::platformDataFromCustomData(FontCustomPlatformData& fontCustomPlatformData, const FontDescription& fontDescription, bool bold, bool italic, const FontFeatureSettings& fontFaceFeatures, FontSelectionSpecifiedCapabilities fontFaceCapabilities)
124{
125 return fontCustomPlatformData.fontPlatformData(fontDescription, bold, italic, fontFaceFeatures, fontFaceCapabilities);
126}
127
128void CachedFont::allClientsRemoved()
129{
130 m_fontCustomPlatformData = nullptr;
131}
132
133void CachedFont::checkNotify(const NetworkLoadMetrics&)
134{
135 if (isLoading())
136 return;
137
138 CachedResourceClientWalker<CachedFontClient> walker(m_clients);
139 while (CachedFontClient* client = walker.next())
140 client->fontLoaded(*this);
141}
142
143bool CachedFont::mayTryReplaceEncodedData() const
144{
145 // If a FontCustomPlatformData has ever been constructed to wrap the internal resource buffer then it still might be in use somewhere.
146 // That platform font object might directly reference the encoded data buffer behind this CachedFont,
147 // so replacing it is unsafe.
148
149 return !m_hasCreatedFontDataWrappingResource;
150}
